projectDescription:
The project is located in Al Amerah area, Al Ain city, southwest of Al Ain Airport.

The project consists of 3 Zones. Imkan was selected to develop zone 1 with a total of 2,350 residential villas, 14 community facilities in addition to roads, services, infrastructure and parks.

•    The project component is as follows:

    •  Total land area 5,130,223 square meters.

    •  Residential villas lands: 2,538,000 square meters.

    •  Amenities lands: 178,916 square meters,

    •  Area of roads and open areas 2,413,307 square meters

    •  14 Community facilities consists of: 4 Mosques, 2 Schools, 2 Nurseries, 1 intermediate clinic, 2 Community Clubs, 1 Police Station, 1 Wedding Hall, 1 Shopping Mall

•      2,350 Residential villa consists of 4 models consisting of:

        •  47 villas (3) rooms with an area of 380-400 square meters.

        •  458 villas (4) rooms with an area of 400-450 square meters.

        •  1,140 villas (5) rooms with an area of 500-510 square meters.

        •  705 villas (6) rooms with an area of 530-550 square meters.
criticalRisks:
Developer (Imkan):

•Contract of Alamerah Development has been signed by Imkan/ ADHA 

Consultants:

•MP Consultant: Draft Contract of Master Planner has been sent to AECOM for review / signature. LOA has been signed by Imkan on 17/03/2025. Awaiting AECOM to sign

MP Consultant: Enabling package is under preparation and expected to be received on 21/03/2025

Project Organization members are interviewed by Imkan. AECOM to hiring in in process.

•Villa Consultant: Competition Of villas (Stage 1 Plans) has been completed. 3 Consultants have been selected to move to next stage 2. Final submission is in 27/03/2025.Presentation to ADHA shall be on 03/04/2025

•Cost consultant RFP is completed, and tender is floated in the market.

•Supervision consultant RFP is completed, and tender is floated in the market.

Contractor:

•Preparation for a meeting between Consultant / Contractor and ADHA is in progress

•A full coordination between Imkan and Contractor (NBHH) is ongoing.

•Project organization candidate have been interviewed, awaiting management decision
developmentUpdate:
Evaluate and award the cost consultant.

Award the Enabling package to the construction contractor and commence the work on site.

Float the supervision consultant in the market.

Finalize the villa competition and select the consultant which will develop the villa designs.

Develop strategy for Amenities / facilities buildings

Develop execution Plan for the Project construction.

projectDescription:
The project is located in Al Amerah area, Al Ain city, southwest of Al Ain Airport.

The enabling package consists of the following:

1- Temporary fence of 5200m

2- Site management (150m*140m) which include site offices, sales center, and material store, in addition to parking for VIP a7 staff. the site offices also include roads, landscape and external works

3- Grading of the site (around 10m3 to be cut and fill)

4- removal of all existing Site obstruction, camel farms, relocation of rainwater outfall, Removal partially the green belt.

6- Site Sign Board.
criticalRisks:
Project Update:

The enabling package has been handed over to the contractor to review / comment.

Site handed over to the contractor on Tuesday 06/05/2025

The overall enabling work progress is as follows:

1- Site survey – Completed & Report submitted.

2- Demarcation – Works Completed.

3- Cut and Fill – 60.5% Completed.

4- Fencing works- 55% Completed.

5- Borehole works Phase.1- Borehole works completed.

6- Site Office – Site Office location has been submitted to ADHA waiting for approval.  

7- NOC – Common NOC borehole, levelling works are cleared.

8- Soil Improvement. – 12.76% Completed.

9- Tree Relocation – Completed, Documentation completed.

10- Borehole works Phase 2 – Permit received.

11- Soil improvement works Phase 2 – Permit received
